parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can cause the occupant to be thrown from the vehicle or not be properly restrained, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt suddenly unbuckles while driving
the seat belt does not latch properly
the seat belt comes loose while driving
the seat belt buckle clicks as if it was locked but comes loose with pressure
the seat belt retracts slowly or not at all
the seat belt breaks or has broken pieces inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause unexpected shifting, hesitation, or failure to shift, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
Incorrect speedometer readings can lead to inaccurate speed information, which can cause accidents, especially when merging or changing lanes.
symptoms: The speedometer displays an incorrect speed
the speedometer is stuck or frozen

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature degradation of rubber seals can lead to water ingress, corrosion, and damage to vehicle components, affecting the overall durability and reliability of the vehicle.
symptoms: often within 3-4 years of vehicle ownership.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The flaking of paint on the hood and bed of the truck can lead to corrosion and damage to the underlying metal, affecting the vehicle's appearance and potentially compromising its structural integrity.
symptoms: Paint on the top surfaces of the truck (hood and bed) flakes off
